    <item>
      <title>URoL:EN — Toward a Unified Theory of Regulatory Functions and Networks</title>
      <link>https://dawoon-jeong0523.github.io/project/urol_en/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 01 Sep 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://dawoon-jeong0523.github.io/project/urol_en/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;NSF-funded URoL:EN project (EF-2133863), developing a unified theory of regulatory functions and networks across biological and social systems. As part of this project, we built a century-scale dataset of the U.S. legal code and analyzed the evolution of its complexity (Jeong et al., &lt;em&gt;Scientific Data&lt;/em&gt;, 2026).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role:&lt;/strong&gt; Researcher&lt;br&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Period:&lt;/strong&gt; Sep 2024 – Aug 2025&lt;br&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Sponsor:&lt;/strong&gt; National Science Foundation (EF-2133863)&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
